A fierce gunbattle between paramilitary troops and renegade tribesmen left eight soldiers dead and 23 others wounded in an insurgency-wracked area of southwestern Pakistan, a troop spokesman said Friday On Sunday, about 3,000 people, mostly women and children of local Bugti tribesmen, also left the town because they fear fresh fighting, said top administrator Abdul Samad Lasi He said they were camped in the open outside Dera Bugti or sheltering with relatives in neighboring towns.
